Sweeping democratic reforms made under the pressure of mass protests have spurred talk  of reuniting the two German states.
The specter of a unified Germany troubles the Poles.
A reported surge of anti-Polish sentiment in East Germany in recent weeks has  heightened anxieties.
Poland's Foreign Minister spoke Thursday and tried to allay the peoples' fears.
He said  that German reunification would not occur in the near future, and when it did, Poland  would insist that a united Germany respect the existing Poland-East German border. 
